WEBVTT

00:01.200 --> 00:02.240
Previously...

00:02.240 --> 00:03.600
Donald, this'll be a big mess.

00:03.600 --> 00:06.280
People are already at the hospital
are talking about this.

00:06.280 --> 00:08.320
Dad's happier since
you two started going out.

00:08.320 --> 00:10.280
Where do you guys go?

00:10.280 --> 00:13.000
You never spend a night together
at our place,

00:13.000 --> 00:15.520
and living with your mom,
your place is out of the question.

00:15.520 --> 00:17.800
I used to be one of the saltiest
cardiac surgeons in the State,

00:17.800 --> 00:20.720
then I lost my temper
and shattered a picture.

00:20.720 --> 00:22.640
Foolish. Now I'm paying the price.

00:22.640 --> 00:25.280
Sidney!

00:25.280 --> 00:27.240
Wayne.

00:27.240 --> 00:28.280
You killed him!

00:28.280 --> 00:29.680
I'll operate.

00:29.680 --> 00:31.080
What?  We have no choice.

00:31.080 --> 00:32.800
I'll just have to dive in.

00:32.800 --> 00:36.800
Clear.

02:09.680 --> 02:13.680
You awake?  Mm.

02:15.520 --> 02:19.520
I can't help thinking about
what happened to Fiscus.

02:19.800 --> 02:22.680
I know the shooting wasn't my fault,
but...

02:22.680 --> 02:26.680
why can't I stop
feeling that way?

02:27.960 --> 02:31.640
Because you expect the best

02:31.640 --> 02:34.120
from the people
who work for you.

02:34.120 --> 02:38.040
And in return, you care about them
so much.

02:38.040 --> 02:40.440
Well, at least
it's quiet now.

02:40.440 --> 02:43.400
I don't know what those people
were doing in the next room.

02:43.400 --> 02:46.680
I just hope they didn't
hurt each other!

02:46.680 --> 02:48.160
You all right?

02:48.160 --> 02:52.160
Mm-hm.

02:52.880 --> 02:56.560
Not the same, is it?

02:56.560 --> 03:00.080
BEEPING

03:00.080 --> 03:04.080
It's mine.

03:06.920 --> 03:09.400
This is Dr Novino.

03:09.400 --> 03:12.480
They beep me, then they put me
on hold.

03:12.480 --> 03:14.400
Sorry. What were
you saying?

03:14.400 --> 03:16.120
I was just thinking.

03:16.120 --> 03:18.800
Yes?

03:18.800 --> 03:21.200
How long?

03:21.200 --> 03:25.200
Um, try some percussion
and postural drainage,

03:26.200 --> 03:29.920
and I'll be right there.

03:29.920 --> 03:33.160
A 12-year-old with CF.

03:33.160 --> 03:35.600
I'm sorry, Donald.
Go ahead.

03:35.600 --> 03:38.480
I was just thinking about
our first time here.

03:38.480 --> 03:41.360
Doctor of the Year awards dinner.
It's not the same, is it?

03:41.360 --> 03:43.040
The hotel's gone downhill.

03:43.040 --> 03:44.720
No, I mean about us.

03:44.720 --> 03:48.280
We just seem to be going
through the motions.

03:48.280 --> 03:52.280
Well, got to go.

03:55.400 --> 03:59.400
Maybe coming here
has lost its magic.

04:10.080 --> 04:12.880
(PRAYS IN HEBREW)

04:12.880 --> 04:15.120
Good morning,
Rabbi Tolchin.

04:15.120 --> 04:16.640
(PRAYS)

04:16.640 --> 04:20.640
Rabbi?

04:21.560 --> 04:25.560
We'll come back later.

04:29.480 --> 04:31.800
Dr Craig, may I say once more
how inspiring it was

04:31.800 --> 04:33.520
to operate beside you last night.

04:33.520 --> 04:34.600
Morrison?

04:34.600 --> 04:35.920
Next case.

04:35.920 --> 04:38.800
Dr Craig.

04:38.800 --> 04:41.200
I was scheduled
to lead the rounds.

04:41.200 --> 04:44.080
Since you were late, we
started without you. Morrison?

04:44.080 --> 04:45.520
I'll take over now.

04:45.520 --> 04:47.400
Dr Kiem, you did
a wonderful job

04:47.400 --> 04:50.240
as Acting Chief
of Surgery.

04:50.240 --> 04:51.440
Now I'm back.

04:51.440 --> 04:53.040
Because you
saved Fiscus?

04:53.040 --> 04:55.640
You're welcome
to tag along.

04:55.640 --> 04:57.520
No, thank you.

04:57.520 --> 05:00.400
Fine. And I'd like to get back
in my old office

05:00.400 --> 05:01.800
as soon as possible.

05:01.800 --> 05:05.040
This afternoon, if it's
not too much trouble.

05:05.040 --> 05:09.040
Come on, Morrison.
Speak up.

05:09.720 --> 05:13.720
MACHINE BEEPING

05:17.800 --> 05:19.720
Any change?  No.

05:19.720 --> 05:22.920
Well, we can only hope
enough oxygen reached his brain.

05:22.920 --> 05:26.120
Mark did a terrific job.
Everybody worked so hard.

05:26.120 --> 05:27.160
Cam I see the chart, please?

05:27.160 --> 05:29.640
(SNIFFLES)

05:29.640 --> 05:31.920
You coming down
with something?

05:31.920 --> 05:34.240
Just a cold.

05:34.240 --> 05:36.800
What about
Wayne's family?

05:36.800 --> 05:40.680
His father's on his way up
from Washington Heights.

05:40.680 --> 05:43.560
Daniel, I've decided
I want to split my job.

05:43.560 --> 05:45.960
I'd like you
to find someone

05:45.960 --> 05:47.880
to head up Medical Education.

05:47.880 --> 05:50.120
I'll remain Director of Medicine.

05:50.120 --> 05:52.760
Give me a little more time
to work with the patients.

05:52.760 --> 05:54.040
&lt; OK.

05:54.040 --> 05:55.880
Oh, by the way,
happy anniversary.

05:55.880 --> 05:57.000
40 years.

05:57.000 --> 06:00.360
I just hope
this young man is alive

06:00.360 --> 06:04.360
to celebrate your 41st.

06:12.200 --> 06:16.200
Katharine and I began our courtship
in these halls...

06:16.640 --> 06:19.360
and linen closets.

06:19.360 --> 06:21.920
1945. She was a volunteer.

06:21.920 --> 06:24.840
I was fresh out of
the South Pacific.

06:24.840 --> 06:27.520
Smitten the moment
I laid eyes on her.

06:27.520 --> 06:30.200
All those years together.
Terrific.

06:30.200 --> 06:32.280
I've only known
Carol a few months...

06:32.280 --> 06:34.440
Nuptials in the offing?

06:34.440 --> 06:37.640
No, I'm afraid our relationship
is losing steam.

06:37.640 --> 06:39.280
Maybe a change
of scenery, huh?

06:39.280 --> 06:40.720
Take the weekend.

06:40.720 --> 06:42.880
I know a lovely inn
in Middlebury.

06:42.880 --> 06:45.600
Always puts us
back on our pins.

06:45.600 --> 06:47.760
The problem's closer to home.

06:47.760 --> 06:50.240
Carol's only been to my house
for dinner,

06:50.240 --> 06:51.640
not the night.

06:51.640 --> 06:53.040
Ah, now I understand.

06:53.040 --> 06:56.800
I don't feel right about bringing
Carol into Maureen's bed.

06:56.800 --> 06:59.080
We bought it when we were
first married.

06:59.080 --> 07:00.920
Started our family there.

07:00.920 --> 07:02.840
She nursed Tommy and Lizzie there.

07:02.840 --> 07:06.640
Cold feet, sick kids,
pet rabbit.

07:06.640 --> 07:08.120
Everything about a marriage

07:08.120 --> 07:10.440
ends up rolled into a mattress,
doesn't it?

07:10.440 --> 07:13.080
I just can't get rid
of the memories, Daniel.

07:13.080 --> 07:17.080
Keep the memories.
Get rid of the bed.

07:21.360 --> 07:24.080
Mr Bevine...?

07:24.080 --> 07:27.040
Yo! Loose set-screw.
Cinched her down.

07:27.040 --> 07:28.640
Thanks.

07:28.640 --> 07:30.920
People walk by a problem
until it's too late.

07:30.920 --> 07:32.360
Like my dad says,

07:32.360 --> 07:36.000
"Routine maintenance
is man's only weapon
against entropy."

07:36.000 --> 07:37.160
Well, I'm Dr Novino.

07:37.160 --> 07:38.560
Italian.

07:38.560 --> 07:41.320
Born, baptised and confirmed
in the North End. Still live there.

07:41.320 --> 07:42.760
My name's Bevine,

07:42.760 --> 07:44.960
but when the boat
left Napoli,

07:44.960 --> 07:46.400
grandpa was a Bovino - cow.

07:46.400 --> 07:47.360
Excuse me?

07:47.360 --> 07:48.800
Excuse me?

07:48.800 --> 07:51.080
Probably explains
the "moo" in "movers".

07:51.080 --> 07:52.840
Bevine and Sons Movers.

07:52.840 --> 07:55.320
"Our boys don't get ripped."

07:55.320 --> 07:57.240
It says so right here.
Keep the pen.

07:57.240 --> 07:59.120
Thank you.

07:59.120 --> 08:01.560
I knew a Novino. Eyes
were different colours.

08:01.560 --> 08:03.640
Bobby. That's Sal's
brother's son.

08:03.640 --> 08:05.560
You live near
Ischia's grocery?

08:05.560 --> 08:08.920
That's my uncle and aunt's.
We're North Street.

08:08.920 --> 08:10.000
We lived on Hull.

08:10.000 --> 08:12.400
My cousins, the Penarellis,
live on Hull.

08:12.400 --> 08:13.960
You're Anna Penarelli's cousin?

08:13.960 --> 08:15.480
Yeah!  Good kid.

08:15.480 --> 08:17.520
I haven't been around
for a while.

08:17.520 --> 08:19.920
Dad hauled us out
to the 'burbs in the '60s.

08:19.920 --> 08:21.160
North End was decaying.

08:21.160 --> 08:22.840
North End was decaying.

08:22.840 --> 08:25.240
Yuppies moved in,
driving prices up.

08:25.240 --> 08:27.280
Normal socioeconomic
change.

08:27.280 --> 08:29.560
My dad likes
to quote Heraclitus.

08:29.560 --> 08:31.920
"All is flux.
Nothing stands still."

08:31.920 --> 08:34.159
Well, neither should I.

08:34.159 --> 08:38.159
Let's see what
you're in here for.

08:39.919 --> 08:41.360
(Ahem.)

08:41.360 --> 08:43.840
Prosthetic placement.

08:43.840 --> 08:46.280
Found out I had
the big C last year.

08:46.280 --> 08:47.800
Dr Barton removed my bladder.

08:47.800 --> 08:49.840
The erectile nerves
to the penis were severed,

08:49.840 --> 08:51.880
rendering me impotent.

08:51.880 --> 08:54.160
Now I'm back for
a penile implant.

08:54.160 --> 08:56.600
Erections will be
artificial,

08:56.600 --> 08:58.320
but my wife and I can have sex
by the numbers again.

08:58.320 --> 08:59.480
One great thing about it...

08:59.480 --> 09:00.560
One great thing about it...

09:00.560 --> 09:03.840
Fastest turnaround time
of any guy on my block.

09:03.840 --> 09:07.840
Oh!

09:44.360 --> 09:48.360
Where am I?

09:48.920 --> 09:51.160
&lt; What's going on?

09:51.160 --> 09:54.160
Please.

09:54.160 --> 09:55.920
It's all right.

09:55.920 --> 09:57.360
Shh. Lie still.

09:57.360 --> 09:59.640
Lie still.

09:59.640 --> 10:03.640
(PRAYS IN HEBREW)

10:04.240 --> 10:06.520
Back again, Rabbi.

10:06.520 --> 10:08.640
Jeez, Louise.

10:08.640 --> 10:10.640
Ehrlich, lead the rounds
to the next patient.

10:10.640 --> 10:11.440
Yes, sir!

10:11.440 --> 10:13.880
Yes, sir!

10:13.880 --> 10:15.720
I'll try...not to. Come on!

10:15.720 --> 10:17.240
(HE PRAYS)

10:17.240 --> 10:19.560
You're not suppose to be
out of bed, Rabbi.

10:19.560 --> 10:23.560
You pulled your EKG out.

10:24.360 --> 10:28.360
Rabbi?

10:29.960 --> 10:31.520
Hello, Mark.

10:31.520 --> 10:33.520
Oh, for crying out loud.

10:33.520 --> 10:37.520
Shh.

10:39.880 --> 10:42.120
The rabbi's davening.

10:42.120 --> 10:44.960
I only have a short time
for rounds.

10:44.960 --> 10:47.840
Orthodox. They're required to pray
three times a day.

10:47.840 --> 10:51.200
The man has a serious health problem
we're trying to assess.

10:51.200 --> 10:53.400
And why am I discussing
this with you?

10:53.400 --> 10:57.320
He requested of my staff
that he be left alone for prayer.

10:57.320 --> 10:59.120
Requested of your staff?

10:59.120 --> 11:01.920
Volunteers of the women's auxiliary
have taken a more active role

11:01.920 --> 11:03.400
in patient relations.

11:03.400 --> 11:05.120
Oh, goody(!)

11:05.120 --> 11:07.080
Wait a minute.
What's that?

11:07.080 --> 11:09.480
The kosher meal he ordered.

11:09.480 --> 11:12.320
All that salt is exactly
what landed the man

11:12.320 --> 11:15.200
on his menorah
in the first place.

11:15.200 --> 11:17.960
I told him, but this is the food
he wants.

11:17.960 --> 11:20.320
The rabbi will make
a speedier recovery

11:20.320 --> 11:24.320
if he's allowed
the comforts of his religion.

11:25.960 --> 11:29.960
It's great to see
your eyes open again.

11:30.000 --> 11:31.400
Cross over to the other side?

11:31.400 --> 11:33.920
I wish I could have
been there to help you.

11:33.920 --> 11:35.360
We didn't let you down.

11:35.360 --> 11:37.280
Hey, bud,
you know what?

11:37.280 --> 11:41.200
You're lucky
to be alive.

11:41.200 --> 11:44.400
Ah, Fiscus.

11:44.400 --> 11:47.240
He's alert, responsive.

11:47.240 --> 11:48.960
Vitals are stable.

11:48.960 --> 11:50.680
Minimal blood
in the drains. &gt;

11:50.680 --> 11:54.680
I'll want to examine
the incision.

12:03.440 --> 12:06.560
Suture line's
straight as an arrow.

12:06.560 --> 12:10.080
(MOANS)

12:10.080 --> 12:14.080
You're a lucky man, Fiscus.

12:21.760 --> 12:25.760
Rounds dismissed.

12:36.960 --> 12:39.120
Hey, hey.

12:39.120 --> 12:43.120
Hey.

12:47.080 --> 12:51.080
Hi. How are you feeling?

12:51.720 --> 12:54.480
Every time I breathe,

12:54.480 --> 12:57.320
I'm afraid the stitches
are going to open up,

12:57.320 --> 12:59.280
and my guts will spill out.

12:59.280 --> 13:03.280
I spoke to your parents.
Your dad's due in any time now.

13:03.800 --> 13:05.840
Why waste the trip?

13:05.840 --> 13:07.480
Wayne, if my son was hurt...

13:07.480 --> 13:08.760
No.

13:08.760 --> 13:12.280
You don't understand.

13:12.280 --> 13:15.000
He should wait.

13:15.000 --> 13:18.360
I'll be back in ER...

13:18.360 --> 13:21.720
..get shot.

13:21.720 --> 13:24.920
Next time you can send me home
in a box.

13:24.920 --> 13:27.680
That's what really gets me. &gt;

13:27.680 --> 13:31.680
I died.

13:31.720 --> 13:35.520
And I'm going
to die again.

13:35.520 --> 13:38.920
We're dying every
day of our lives.

13:38.920 --> 13:41.320
When it's over...

13:41.320 --> 13:45.320
(EXHALES LOUDLY)

13:47.040 --> 13:49.920
Won't even be able
to do this.

13:49.920 --> 13:52.120
Simplest things.

13:52.120 --> 13:55.200
We all face that
knowledge, you know,

13:55.200 --> 13:58.200
but we keep going.

13:58.200 --> 14:02.200
How?

14:06.840 --> 14:09.760
Please...

14:09.760 --> 14:13.760
Leave me alone.

14:20.640 --> 14:22.160
Helen.

14:22.160 --> 14:25.080
Mark and I are agreed - we want
to move Fiscus out of the ICU

14:25.080 --> 14:27.000
and into a regular room.

14:27.000 --> 14:28.440
I think he'll bounce back faster

14:28.440 --> 14:31.360
if he's not being treated
as a critical patient.

14:31.360 --> 14:33.240
By the way,
I'll be out this afternoon.

14:33.240 --> 14:35.000
Another medical conference?

14:35.000 --> 14:36.320
Another medical conference?

14:36.320 --> 14:40.320
TANNOY ANOUNCEMENTS

14:41.160 --> 14:42.360
Daniel?

14:42.360 --> 14:44.760
Why'd the Braves
ever leave Boston?

14:44.760 --> 14:48.760
How should I know?
I want to talk with you.

14:52.760 --> 14:55.160
About that spouse of yours.

14:55.160 --> 14:58.520
There's a liver that's not long
for this world.

14:58.520 --> 14:59.600
Mine.

14:59.600 --> 15:01.560
Oh.

15:01.560 --> 15:03.560
Well, it's not
really my field.

15:03.560 --> 15:06.760
The cancer's neither
advanced nor retreated.

15:06.760 --> 15:08.760
What about Katharine?

15:08.760 --> 15:10.880
Well, I have
an Orthodox rabbi in

15:10.880 --> 15:13.000
for acute hypertension.

15:13.000 --> 15:15.400
Katharine is helping him
commit ritual suicide

15:15.400 --> 15:17.480
on kosher corned beef.

15:17.480 --> 15:20.560
Orthodox law
is hardly her fault.

15:20.560 --> 15:23.280
Katharine is helpful.
She's concerned.

15:23.280 --> 15:25.680
And in the way.
Doctors ran St Eligius,

15:25.680 --> 15:28.080
but she and
her merry volunteers

15:28.080 --> 15:31.160
are turning this hospital
into a cruise ship.

15:31.160 --> 15:34.000
Before you know it,
we'll be having costume night.

15:34.000 --> 15:37.880
Volunteerism is the cornerstone
of American philanthropy.

15:37.880 --> 15:40.720
Don't hand me reheated
Reagan, Daniel.

15:40.720 --> 15:44.080
You won't say anything
because she's your wife.

15:44.080 --> 15:46.040
Katharine has spent
countless hours

15:46.040 --> 15:48.000
organizing the
auxiliary's activities.

15:48.000 --> 15:51.480
Teas, luncheons, award dinners -
no problems.

15:51.480 --> 15:55.480
Just tell her to keep her butt
out of my patient's treatment.

16:11.440 --> 16:13.560
Mr Bevine, Dr Novino,
you're both here.

16:13.560 --> 16:15.480
Practising.

16:15.480 --> 16:18.200
Mr Bevine has chosen
to treat his impotence

16:18.200 --> 16:20.600
with the inflatable
penile prosthesis.

16:20.600 --> 16:23.560
His other option would
be the more common,

16:23.560 --> 16:26.640
less expensive,
semi-rigid implant,

16:26.640 --> 16:28.840
which is flexible
and can be bent

16:28.840 --> 16:30.600
into position
like a gooseneck lamp.

16:30.600 --> 16:34.000
Even though the inflatable
is costly and can break down,

16:34.000 --> 16:36.920
it more closely duplicates
a natural erection.

16:36.920 --> 16:40.920
I'll make a small incision
near the base of the penis.

16:41.000 --> 16:43.880
The entire apparatus is implanted
through the one opening.

16:43.880 --> 16:45.600
Any questions?

16:45.600 --> 16:47.120
Seems pretty straight ahead.

16:47.120 --> 16:49.600
Good. Then I'll see you
both in surgery.

16:49.600 --> 16:51.160
Oh, Carol,

16:51.160 --> 16:54.080
the next time you're out
with Dr Westphall,

16:54.080 --> 16:56.440
put in a good word
for urology.

16:56.440 --> 16:59.640
We should have
a lithotripter.

16:59.640 --> 17:01.040
Donald Westphall.

17:01.040 --> 17:04.400
Moved him back into his house
a year ago.

17:04.400 --> 17:05.839
Stuffer, not a packer.

17:05.839 --> 17:07.760
You two are an item?

17:07.760 --> 17:09.680
We're a headline
around here.

17:09.680 --> 17:11.119
Jeez, love in the workplace.

17:11.119 --> 17:14.400
Perilous. Destroyed two
of my best moving men.

17:14.400 --> 17:15.760
In love with the same woman?

17:15.760 --> 17:19.760
Each other.

17:21.319 --> 17:24.359
I'm anxious to get my pay cheque -
it always depresses me.

17:24.359 --> 17:26.880
Never enough, especially
with my new family.

17:26.880 --> 17:30.080
Boomer, how can you feed three more
on our salary?

17:30.080 --> 17:33.040
With Robert gone, alone,
I can barely make ends meet.

17:33.040 --> 17:37.040
Got to get my pay cheque in the bank
before my balance hits the minimum.

17:43.360 --> 17:46.120
And we're worried
about money.

17:46.120 --> 17:49.400
Poor Wayne - he never hurt anything.

17:49.400 --> 17:52.480
Last night, Wayne was
catching fireflies

17:52.480 --> 17:54.480
like a kid
filled with energy.

17:54.480 --> 17:56.400
The woman who shot him
should be punished.

17:56.400 --> 17:58.840
What can we do for him?

17:58.840 --> 18:02.840
Wayne's always meant
so much to me.

18:04.760 --> 18:06.120
Coming, Boomer?

18:06.120 --> 18:10.120
No, I'm gonna go back up.
Gonna see how Wayne's doing.

18:21.840 --> 18:23.800
Wayne's been
my best friend.

18:23.800 --> 18:25.200
I love the guy.

18:25.200 --> 18:27.160
Me, too.

18:27.160 --> 18:30.520
Hey, subtraction
was off! I'm way above

18:30.520 --> 18:34.520
my minimum bank balance
of Â¤5,000.

18:37.920 --> 18:39.400
What's all this?

18:39.400 --> 18:40.840
My medical texts.

18:40.840 --> 18:42.800
I thought everything was stolen
along with your manuscript.

18:42.800 --> 18:44.720
Lucky for me, these were
in the basement.

18:44.720 --> 18:47.280
But I'm putting that chapter
behind me

18:47.280 --> 18:49.800
with the 18
John Doe pirated.

18:49.800 --> 18:52.040
Forget him...

18:52.040 --> 18:56.040
and Paulette Kiem.

18:58.400 --> 19:00.720
Thank you.

19:00.720 --> 19:02.680
Why aren't you packed?

19:02.680 --> 19:06.040
We got the embassy personnel
