to accommodate your special needs.

32:54.160 --> 32:55.880
Are my requests
so intrusive?

32:55.880 --> 32:58.320
When they interfere with
proper medical care, yes.

32:58.320 --> 33:02.120
Please. I'm dying. I won't be
bothering you much longer.

33:02.120 --> 33:04.520
Dr Craig told me you were only
hypertensive.

33:04.520 --> 33:06.280
He ordered a CT scan
this afternoon

33:06.280 --> 33:09.120
after finding a lump
in my chest.

33:09.120 --> 33:10.880
The cancer is everywhere.

33:10.880 --> 33:14.640
I'll live less than a year.

33:14.640 --> 33:18.640
But why are you so angry at me
for practising my faith?

33:18.880 --> 33:21.600
I was raised Orthodox.

33:21.600 --> 33:23.840
Something happened,
I assume.

33:23.840 --> 33:26.840
Margaret Ryan.

33:26.840 --> 33:29.040
I see.

33:29.040 --> 33:33.040
We feel in love.
I wanted to marry her.

33:35.360 --> 33:37.560
The rabbi condemned.

33:37.560 --> 33:41.360
My parents forbade.

33:41.360 --> 33:42.800
I lost her.

33:42.800 --> 33:44.680
For all my devotion to God,

33:44.680 --> 33:48.360
I was deprived of happiness.

33:48.360 --> 33:52.280
I never went to temple again.

33:52.280 --> 33:53.800
You could have married her anyway.

33:53.800 --> 33:57.080
In a sense, I did.

33:57.080 --> 34:00.040
Many years later
I met my wife.

34:00.040 --> 34:02.560
We wed in the Catholic church.

34:02.560 --> 34:04.480
Dr Auschlander,

34:04.480 --> 34:07.160
I'm sorry you felt
so betrayed,

34:07.160 --> 34:10.800
but there's no fault.
Orthodoxy tries to preserve

34:10.800 --> 34:13.320
a pure ethnic and
religious Judaism.

34:13.320 --> 34:15.120
You're feelings
didn't coincide,

34:15.120 --> 34:16.320
so you walked away.

34:16.320 --> 34:19.480
Religion is there
when people need guidance.

34:19.480 --> 34:22.880
In moments of crisis, a death...

34:22.880 --> 34:26.400
faith offers comfort.

34:26.400 --> 34:30.400
I'd like to pray now.

34:51.040 --> 34:52.440
That's it.

34:52.440 --> 34:53.400
Thank you.

34:53.400 --> 34:54.679
Thank you.

34:54.679 --> 34:58.680
No, why don't you see if you can
find a place in the basement.

34:58.720 --> 34:59.920
Sure, if you want.

34:59.920 --> 35:03.920
Somebody might be able to use it.

35:34.960 --> 35:36.240
Have you seen Carol?

35:36.240 --> 35:40.240
She should be out of surgery.

35:41.840 --> 35:44.920
Donald, do you
have a moment?

35:44.920 --> 35:48.920
Barely. I'm on my way
to talk with Carol.

35:50.720 --> 35:53.920
Do you ever regret
leaving the Catholic church?

35:53.920 --> 35:56.800
       Huh! You want just a  moment
to discuss Catholicism?

35:56.800 --> 36:00.160
I'm sorry. It's been
a full day for me.

36:00.160 --> 36:04.160
I've got a head full of Carol,
Maureen and that bed.

36:04.520 --> 36:07.240
Do I regret it?

36:07.240 --> 36:08.840
Yes, I do, sometimes.

36:08.840 --> 36:11.920
Especially when I think of
Lizzie's first communion.

36:11.920 --> 36:13.680
It's still ingrained in me.

36:13.680 --> 36:16.200
The other day, coming in,
I almost hit a fellow

36:16.200 --> 36:19.680
that ran a red light.
I instinctively crossed myself.

36:19.680 --> 36:23.080
Today I was with a man
dying of cancer,

36:23.080 --> 36:25.480
but you never would
have known it.

36:25.480 --> 36:28.760
He was calm, content,
renewed by his religion.

36:28.760 --> 36:31.520
Sounds like Father McCabe.

36:31.520 --> 36:35.520
And I wonder...by running away
from my faith,

36:36.200 --> 36:37.960
did I deprive myself

36:37.960 --> 36:40.240
of the strength needed
to face death?

36:40.240 --> 36:42.080
You've been very strong,
my friend.

36:42.080 --> 36:45.040
But what if we're
missing something?

36:45.040 --> 36:48.040
Should the end of my life be
reconciled to the beginning?

36:48.040 --> 36:49.320
It's up to you, isn't it?

36:49.320 --> 36:50.760
Oh, by the way, I saw Katharine.

36:50.760 --> 36:54.760
First thing  I'd  do
is make up with her.

36:58.080 --> 37:00.680
(TV) 'Let me
centre the ball.

37:00.680 --> 37:03.240
'OK. 1, 2, 3, hut!

37:03.240 --> 37:06.120
'Now, Bullwinkle.
Alley-oop!

37:06.120 --> 37:08.920
'Well, it was the alley-oop
that did it.'

37:08.920 --> 37:10.760
Funny stuff.

37:10.760 --> 37:13.200
How come it's not on any more?

37:13.200 --> 37:16.040
You're not laughing.

37:16.040 --> 37:17.960
When you were a kid,

37:17.960 --> 37:21.800
we thought you were messed up.
You laughed at everything,

37:21.800 --> 37:25.000
even at your grandmother's funeral.

37:25.000 --> 37:27.800
I finally see Grandma's
point of view.

37:27.800 --> 37:31.400
Well, you had your own way
of looking at the world.

37:31.400 --> 37:34.280
I just didn't understand that
at the time.

37:34.280 --> 37:36.120
Makes sense.

37:36.120 --> 37:40.120
This is the longest
we've been together alone.

37:41.080 --> 37:42.440
Look, we're different.

37:42.440 --> 37:44.880
I was raised by
Lithuanian immigrants.

37:44.880 --> 37:48.080
Good people, but
with old-world values.

37:48.080 --> 37:50.160
You, you're so American,
so modern.

37:50.160 --> 37:54.160
Ringo, Batman, bubble gum,
all that goofiness.

37:54.960 --> 37:57.760
I just didn't relate.

37:57.760 --> 37:59.200
You could've tried.

37:59.200 --> 38:02.000
You never did anything
with me.

38:02.000 --> 38:04.040
Yes, I did.

38:04.040 --> 38:06.880
Right. You took me to
Grant's Tomb one Saturday.

38:06.880 --> 38:10.000
And you laughed all day long...

38:10.000 --> 38:12.760
"Who's buried in Grant's Tomb?
Ha-ha-ha."

38:12.760 --> 38:14.720
You drove me crazy
with your jokes.

38:14.720 --> 38:18.720
DOOR OPENS

38:20.280 --> 38:22.200
Victor?

38:22.200 --> 38:26.200
Hey, Dr Fiscus.

38:34.280 --> 38:35.440
Look, son...

38:35.440 --> 38:37.920
I finally understand.

38:37.920 --> 38:41.920
Truth is, you never liked me.

38:50.720 --> 38:52.560
Looking good, Jack!

38:52.560 --> 38:55.280
Want to grab a beer?
I'm meeting Joanne.

38:55.280 --> 38:57.720
I wish I could. Plans.

38:57.720 --> 38:59.280
Hi.

38:59.280 --> 39:01.480
Hi.

39:01.480 --> 39:03.440
We're not supposed to meet
for another hour, right?

39:03.440 --> 39:06.800
No, right.

39:06.800 --> 39:10.800
Boy, with Dr Barton, you're in
and out of surgery in no time.

39:11.320 --> 39:14.400
By the way, he wants
a new lithotripter.

39:14.400 --> 39:18.400
That'd sure come in handy.

39:19.680 --> 39:22.160
Ah...sure.

39:22.160 --> 39:24.080
Well, got to go.

39:24.080 --> 39:28.080
Yeah. Bye.

39:28.400 --> 39:31.880
&lt; Something the matter?

39:31.880 --> 39:35.640
Carol, I've been thinking
things over.

39:35.640 --> 39:37.680
It doesn't make sense for us
to keep seeing each other.

39:37.680 --> 39:39.840
What?

39:39.840 --> 39:41.400
I'm just not happy.

39:41.400 --> 39:42.800
But Donald...

39:42.800 --> 39:45.200
The difference in our age, &gt;

39:45.200 --> 39:49.200
and we never seem to really
have time together.

39:51.040 --> 39:55.040
Maureen is still inside me.

39:55.360 --> 39:57.280
I thought that's
what you wanted -

39:57.280 --> 39:58.760
to start seeing someone else.

39:58.760 --> 40:00.480
Yeah, it was, for a while.

40:00.480 --> 40:04.480
But I just think a clean break
would be good for both of us.

40:06.400 --> 40:09.880
Give us some time to think
about where we are. OK?

40:09.880 --> 40:11.560
You sure?

40:11.560 --> 40:15.560
Well, if it's what you want, but...

40:15.840 --> 40:19.840
You've been a good pal.

40:20.920 --> 40:22.080
You've been a good pal.

40:22.080 --> 40:26.080
You've been a good pal.

40:47.400 --> 40:50.000
Barton told me I won't be able to
test-drive the prosthesis

40:50.000 --> 40:51.560
for a week or so.

40:51.560 --> 40:53.760
Be in too much pain.

40:53.760 --> 40:54.840
Hiya, Jonas.

40:54.840 --> 40:57.520
Hi, Victor.

40:57.520 --> 40:59.920
Not many places
you can smoke any more.

40:59.920 --> 41:02.800
I ended up by
the cafeteria dumpster.

41:02.800 --> 41:05.640
Met a Dr Craig.
He a big deal?

41:05.640 --> 41:07.440
Around here.

41:07.440 --> 41:10.040
He says you're gonna have
a complete recovery.

41:10.040 --> 41:11.440
You could have asked me.

41:11.440 --> 41:13.360
I'm a doctor.

41:13.360 --> 41:15.760
Yeah, but... Anyway,
the important thing is

41:15.760 --> 41:19.000
you're going to be OK.

41:19.000 --> 41:20.680
And it's getting late.

41:20.680 --> 41:22.000
You can go.

41:22.000 --> 41:23.160
Sure?

41:23.160 --> 41:26.080
Yeah.

41:26.080 --> 41:30.080
Well, I'll be
staying overnight, uh...

41:32.240 --> 41:34.520
Look, how much more
do I have to do

41:34.520 --> 41:37.640
to show you that I care?

41:37.640 --> 41:40.280
What you said before,
you were right.

41:40.280 --> 41:42.600
I never liked you.

41:42.600 --> 41:43.600
I knew it.

41:43.600 --> 41:47.600
I knew it.

42:00.600 --> 42:02.760
Donald, we've got a problem.

42:02.760 --> 42:04.800
I know, Paulette -
Helen already told me.

42:04.800 --> 42:07.560
I talked to Daniel.
He spoke with Judge Farnham.

42:07.560 --> 42:08.840
Where the heck was I?

42:08.840 --> 42:10.120
I don't know.

42:10.120 --> 42:11.560
At least she's out, right?

42:11.560 --> 42:13.000
I'm splitting my job.

42:13.000 --> 42:14.920
Paulette will run
Medical Education.

42:14.920 --> 42:18.000
She's good with the Residents
and she'll do a good job.

42:18.000 --> 42:19.240
Ah, for the love of mon...

42:19.240 --> 42:22.160
Ah, for the love of mon...

42:22.160 --> 42:23.800
You look like hell.
Are you all right?

42:23.800 --> 42:26.200
You look like hell.
Are you all right?

42:26.200 --> 42:27.680
Carol and I said goodbye,
all right?

42:27.680 --> 42:28.960
She pulled the plug?

42:28.960 --> 42:30.480
No, it was my doing.

42:30.480 --> 42:32.200
I thought you were
ass over tea kettle for the girl?

42:32.200 --> 42:33.400
Of course I am.

42:33.400 --> 42:35.080
&lt; Then why'd you call it off?

42:35.080 --> 42:37.000
Because she never would have.

42:37.000 --> 42:38.080
The relationship's
no good for her.

42:38.080 --> 42:39.320
The relationship's
no good for her.

42:39.320 --> 42:43.320
How come I never get
what I want?

42:57.160 --> 42:59.680
&lt; Dying to try this out.

42:59.680 --> 43:01.000
&lt; Here we go.

43:01.000 --> 43:02.520
AIR PASSES THROUGH PUMP

43:02.520 --> 43:05.320
&lt; Anticipation.

43:05.320 --> 43:08.960
&lt; Mm... Stimulation.

43:08.960 --> 43:11.800
&lt; Arousal!

43:11.800 --> 43:14.320
&lt; Not bad.

43:14.320 --> 43:18.160
&lt; Now, let's see what this baby
can really do.

43:18.160 --> 43:20.640
&lt; Arousal.

43:20.640 --> 43:22.760
&lt; Big heat.

43:22.760 --> 43:25.840
&lt; Going crazy!

43:25.840 --> 43:27.800
&lt; Maxed out!

43:27.800 --> 43:29.520
BANG

43:29.520 --> 43:32.520
&lt; Uh-oh.

43:32.520 --> 43:36.520
&lt; Boy, that hurts.

